<h2 id="flex">Flex</h2>

<p>The shorthand property, <code>flex</code> encompasses three properties: <code>flex-grow</code>, <code>flex-shrink</code>, and <code>flex-basis</code>, respectively. There are several options for creating ratios for flex items. However, these ratios are imprecise, so should not be used if specific widths are desired.</p>

<div class="site-showcase">
<div class="site-showcase__header">
  <h3 class="site-showcase__heading">Flex</h3>
  <ul class="site-utility-scope">
    <li class="site-utility-scope__item">
      
        <a class="site-utility-scope__button site-utility-scope__button--supported" href="#responsive-prefixes"><i class="fas fa-check-circle" aria-label="Is"></i> Responsive</a>
      
    </li>
  </ul>
  <p class="site-showcase__prop-head">CSS property: <span class="site-showcase__prop">flex</span></p>
</div>

